social_posts.post_text:
“The Brazilian Jiu Jitsu purple belt is the toughest belt to achieve in any martial art”

- Frank Ungaro

As I stepped forward on the mats, last Saturday, when @mistral_g  @dominic_cotebjj and @bjjpiero called my name, the peeps behind me, my rolling partners, roared. They surprised me. I stopped and took a deep breath because I was overwhelmed with emotions. I swallowed my tears but only because I had something to say. 

The appreciation I have for those people is impossible to put in words. In the moment, I realized that the appreciation was mutual. 

It’s an odd but wonderful thing to show up in a small room expecting to get choked out by multiple trained killers and feel completely at peace. 

My coaches were calling me up to give me my purple belt. After many years, thousands of hours of training,  thousands of sparring sessions, hundreds of submissions, some cauliflower ears and some medals, I finally earned my first advanced belt. 

I am whole and I extremely thankful! @three_headed_beast @teamevolutionhq
